==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imido
<hw>Im"i*do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, containing, or combined with, the radical NH, which
is called the <xex>imido group</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Imido acid</b></col>, <cd>an organic acid, consisting of
one or more acid radicals so united with the imido group that it
contains replaceable acid hydrogen, and plays the part of an acid;
<as>as, uric acid, succinimide, etc., are <ex>imido
acids</ex></as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imitability</ent>⟦br⟧
